		Updating the views for A(y[],@rule-0,A,B,@rule-1,@rule-2)

	Applying rule #[@rule-0 && A && B]create A (File "example_working_set.ka", line 6, characters 0-37:):
		the precondition is satisfied

	Applying rule #[@rule-1]phosphorization (File "example_working_set.ka", line 7, characters 0-40:):
		the precondition is satisfied

		Updating the views for A(x{},@rule-0,A,B,@rule-1,@rule-2)

	Applying rule #[@rule-2]binding x (File "example_working_set.ka", line 8, characters 0-52:):
		the precondition is satisfied

		Updating the views for A(x[],@rule-0,A,B,@rule-1,@rule-2)

		Updating the views for A(x[],@rule-0,A,B,@rule-1,@rule-2)

	Applying rule binding y (File "example_working_set.ka", line 10, characters 0-52:):
		the precondition is satisfied

		Updating the views for A(y[],@rule-0,A,B,@rule-1,@rule-2)

		Updating the views for A(y[],@rule-0,A,B,@rule-1,@rule-2)

------------------------------------------------------------
* There are some non applyable rules
------------------------------------------------------------
rule create A (File "example_working_set.ka", line 6, characters 0-37:) could be applied if @rule-0.and.A.and.B.
rule phosphorization (File "example_working_set.ka", line 7, characters 0-40:) could be applied if @rule-0.and.A.and.B.and.@rule-1.
rule binding x (File "example_working_set.ka", line 8, characters 0-52:) could be applied if @rule-0.and.A.and.B.and.@rule-2.
rule binding y (File "example_working_set.ka", line 10, characters 0-52:) could be applied if @rule-0.and.A.and.B.

------------------------------------------------------------
* There are some non creatable agents 
------------------------------------------------------------
A can occur in the model if @rule-0.and.A.and.B.

